{
  "text": "where\u00ea R and\u00ea L represent the states of circular polarization, right (RCP) and left (LCP), respectively [CITATION_1] . Angle \u03c7 varies between 0 and \u03c0\u22152. The usefulness of this representation is that the two variables, \u03c7 and \u03b8, specify the shape and orientation of the ellipse, respectively. The ratio of the amplitudes of the polarization components is related to the ellipticity of the state by",
